  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As discussed in https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/pull/1751, the tests that include send and receive hooks are only performed on `send` and `operatorSend`, skipping `transfer` and `transferFrom`. \r\n\r\nThese are in the 'send and receive hooks' `describe` block, with the actual tests in the behavior functions `shouldBehaveLikeERC777SendBurnWithSendHook` and `shouldBehaveLikeERC777SendBurnMintInternalWithReceiveHook`.\r\n\r\nWe should probably create two additional functions, similar to these, with two main differences: these calls should not fail when the recipient is a contract that doesn't implement the interface, and both `userData` and `operatorData` are empty.",
